From 9b5813c3dd3a27e7963eb455f095a400449d4396 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 22:46:41 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 38/40] inline-3d(#625): drop the eye feed the rig migration
 orphaned, and the diags

Once the renderer stopped rebuilding Kooima and started consuming the runtime's
views (XR_DXR_view_rig on a zone-scoped locate), the whole eye-delivery chain
lost its only consumer. xrLocateViews resolves eyes server-side, so nothing
needs the eyes shipped to the renderer at all:

  GPU submit -> ReportEyesToBrowser -> mojo ReportInline3DEyes ->
  DisplayXRWeaverImpl -> SetEyesFromGpu -> browser-side latest_eyes cache ->
  GetLatest -> DisplayXRService::GetLatestEyes -> renderer

Every link is now dead. Removed, along with DisplayXRDisplayInfo and
GetLatest's DisplayInfo::element_* -- the display-relative rebase (ClientToScreen
origin + metres-per-pixel) that only the deleted projection math consumed, and
that was the actual source of the element-geometry bug. The rig path feeds the
runtime the window-client weave rect verbatim instead, so there is no second
coordinate derivation left in the tree to disagree with the first.

Also drops the TEMP DIAG logging (the inline3d gate / rig-views VLOGs). It did
its job -- comparing __wall.session.requestAnimationFrame against
document.requestAnimationFrame is what proved the frame loop was dead -- but it
is not shippable instrumentation.

Net -296 lines. No behaviour change: this is all code nothing calls.
